TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {3569=The 2013 Arizona Cardinals season was the franchise's 94th season in the National Football League, the 26th in Arizona and the first under head coach Bruce Arians. The team finished with a 10–6 record, which was the second time in 37 years that the team finished with at least 10 wins. The Cardinals doubled their win total from 2012, and were in playoff contention heading into the Week 17 regular season finale, but missed the playoffs for a fourth consecutive season., 167282=Media related to 2013 Arizona Cardinals season at Wikimedia Commons}
